{"author":"Joe Oakhart","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Context\nA first-class `identity` entity on rebar's event machinery, modeled on the\n`session_log` / `code_review` exemption pattern: gate / lifecycle / graph /\nJira-sync exempt. It holds a display name, an email, a list of provider\nmappings, and a list of public keys, keyed by an opaque rebar ticket id. This is\nthe foundational data structure the rest of the epic builds on (event\n`author_id`, authorship attestations, key-rotation eras, Jira accountId mapping).\n\n## Why\nAuthorship certification and provider-neutral user mapping both need one durable\nhome for \"who a contributor is\" that is not itself dispatchable work. Reusing the\nticket substrate (like `session_log`) gives event-sourcing, replication, and\n`show`/`search` for free without polluting the dependency graph or Jira sync.\n\n## What\nIntroduce `identity` as a new exempt ticket-type, a create path, and a\nself-identity config pointer.\n\n### 1. Register `identity` as an exempt ticket-type (mirror session_log/code_review)\nAdd the type at EVERY site the existing exempt types appear (grounded, verified\nfile:line list — omitting any one leaves a seam silently un-patched):\n- `src/rebar/schemas/common.schema.json` `$defs/ticket_type` enum — SOURCE OF TRUTH.\n- `src/rebar/types.py` is GENERATED — regenerate via `python -m rebar.schemas.gen_types`\n  (never hand-edit); confirm `TicketType` now includes `identity`.\n- `src/rebar/_commands/composer.py:34` `_TYPES` tuple (accepts `create`), AND\n  `:41` `_FILE_IMPACT_EXEMPT_TYPES` (so create emits no spurious no-file_impact nudge).\n- `src/rebar/reducer/_api.py:23` `_NON_GRAPH_ARTIFACT_TYPES` (drop from graph/health).\n- `src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/config.py:13` `EXCLUDED_SYNC_TYPES`.\n- `src/rebar/_engine_support/gates.py:26` `_GATE_EXEMPT_TYPES` (the shared constant\n  the three per-ticket gates check_ac/clarity_check/quality_check consult).\n- `src/rebar/_commands/gates.py:118` inline `(\"bug\",\"session_log\",\"code_review\")`\n  tuple in `claim_gate_check()` (the plan-review START-WORK gate on claim/transition).\n- `src/rebar/_commands/transition_close.py:99` inline `(\"session_log\",\"code_review\")`\n  tuple in the completion-verification close-gate pre-check.\n- `src/rebar/llm/plan_review/orchestrator.py:563` inline drift_refresh guard AND the\n  `workflow_ops.py:79` exempt tuple.\nNone of these inline tuples delegate to `_NON_GRAPH_ARTIFACT_TYPES`, so each is a\ndiscrete edit. Excluded from `ready`/`next_batch`/default `list` follows\nstructurally from the graph exemption (same mechanism as `session_log`).\nRecommended: where practical, route the new inline tuples through one shared\nconstant to prevent future drift (implementer's discretion; not required by AC).\n\n### 2. Create path (`rebar identity create` + library + MCP)\nA single CREATE event mints an identity carrying:\n- `name`: str (display name)   - `email`: str\n- `mappings`: list of `{\"provider\": str, \"external_id\": str}`. `provider` is an\n  OPEN lowercase-string vocabulary (well-known `jira`/`github`/`gitea`; not a\n  closed enum). `external_id` is the provider's opaque stable id (NEVER an email).\n  CLI: repeatable `--mapping <provider>:<external_id>` (first colon splits;\n  `external_id` may contain colons).\n- `keys`: list of OpenSSH authorized-keys public-key line strings\n  (`\"ssh-ed25519 AAAA...\"`). The key-type is embedded in the line itself; NO\n  separate `algorithm` field (avoids duplicating/desyncing it). The foundation\n  attest scheme name is `sshsig`; the key-type token is parsed from the line by\n  downstream verify (bde5).\n`show` renders name/email/mappings/keys. (The provider vocabulary and\nauthorized-keys key format are recorded as an ADR in sibling task 4b5b; this\nticket adopts the above defaults.)\n\n### 3. Self-identity config pointer (`.rebar/current_identity`)\n- **Path**: `.rebar/current_identity` (`.rebar/` is already git-ignored via\n  `.gitignore:11`; mirrors `.rebar/current_session_log`, see\n  `src/rebar/_commands/session_log.py`). No gitignore edit needed.\n- **Format**: JSON `{\"identity_id\": \"<ticket_id>\"}` (extra keys tolerated).\n- **Write path**: `rebar identity use <id>` writes the pointer; `rebar identity\n  create --self` writes it to the just-created identity in the same invocation.\n- **Resolution — `resolve_current_identity() -> Optional[str]`**:\n  1. Pointer file present AND names an existing `identity` ticket -> that id.\n  2. Else match `git config user.email` (exact, case-insensitive) vs identity\n     `email` fields.\n- **Fallbacks (all return `None`; identity is opt-in so unauthenticated is a\n  valid state, never an error)**: git email unset/unconfigured -> `None`;\n  the `git config` subprocess errors (git missing, OSError, non-zero exit,\n  timeout) -> `None` (caught, not propagated); zero identities match -> `None`;\n  >=2 match -> `None` + a WARNING naming the ambiguity; pointer names a\n  deleted/absent identity -> fall through to git-email match, else `None`.\n- **Export side-effect (accepted)**: adding `identity` to\n  `_NON_GRAPH_ARTIFACT_TYPES` hides identity tickets from default NDJSON export,\n  opt-in via the existing `--include-session-logs` flag — same posture as\n  `session_log`; acceptable for this ticket (no new flag).\n\n## Scope\nIn: type registration at all listed sites, the create path (CLI/lib/MCP), `show`\nrendering, the pointer write + resolver + fallbacks. Out: event `author_id`\n(4e9d), authorship signing (bde5), key rotation (e165), Jira mapping (264f/2f13),\nenforcement (3183).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `identity` is registered at all listed sites and is exempt from\n  lifecycle/gates/graph/Jira-sync (mirrors session_log); a test asserts an\n  `identity` ticket is absent from `ready`/`next_batch`/default `list` and that\n  `check_ac`/`clarity_check`/`quality_check` return pass for it.\n- [ ] A create path (`rebar identity create` + `rebar.create_identity` + MCP)\n  mints an identity in one CREATE carrying name, email, mappings, keys; a test\n  round-trips create then asserts `rebar show <id> --output llm` (structured\n  JSON) contains all four fields with the created values.\n- [ ] `resolve_current_identity()` reads `.rebar/current_identity`\n  (`{\"identity_id\": ...}`) when present, else matches `git config user.email`\n  case-insensitively; a test asserts (a) pointer hit, (b) git-email default hit,\n  (c) each fallback (no email / subprocess error / zero match / multiple match /\n  dangling pointer) returns `None` without raising.\n\n## file_impact\n- `src/rebar/schemas/common.schema.json`, `src/rebar/types.py` (regenerated)\n- `src/rebar/_commands/composer.py` (_TYPES + _FILE_IMPACT_EXEMPT_TYPES + create)\n- `src/rebar/reducer/_api.py`, `src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/config.py`\n- `src/rebar/_engine_support/gates.py`, `src/rebar/_commands/gates.py`,\n  `src/rebar/_commands/transition_close.py`\n- `src/rebar/llm/plan_review/orchestrator.py` + `workflow_ops.py`\n- new identity module (create path + resolver) + CLI/lib/MCP wiring"}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1783816054368467001,"uuid":"97f08871-8740-4a49-aa47-bd9560d08a14"}